messages.text: I understand that patients are naturally curious about their therapists, but my personal life is not relevant to your therapy.
I will not discuss it with you.
Your husband was killed by a drunk driver.
I have boundaries I expect you to respect.
I wouldn't have kept talking about it.
You are allowed to talk about the issues you are going through.
But I could have upset you by talking about it.
You do not need to worry about me.
We are here to focus on you.
I'm sorry I looked into it.
Why do you think you did?
I wanted to know if you were married.
And see if your husband looked at all like me.
Can you say more about that?
I'm not here to judge you.
I think my brother knows I've been talking to you.
He might have remotely hacked into my computer.
I'm not great with the internet but I can tell when I'm being spied on.
This is a secure connection, patientzero.
He did it at school when report cards were due.
I guess I didn't think he'd be looking to get into mine.
But the mugshot made him angry.
And by now he's seen the threats.
I told you I was going to kill him.
And how do you feel about it now?
If he knows all this, he's coming for me.
I go, and it is done; the bell invites me.
I'm afraid I don't understand. The bell?
He's about to kill the King of Scotland.
Are you still thinking of killing your brother?
I've never felt such a sense of calm.
Either way, I won't be coming back to you.
Are you thinking of hurting yourself?
But either he will kill me.
Or I will be on the lam.
I don't know who you are but let me help you.
He said to tell you hello.
Are you sure he meant me?
He said to "tell Hortence hello for me."
So yeah, I'm pretty fucking sure.
If I don't kill him, he's going to come for you next.
The records belong to SafeHaven, not to me.
No, this is all too much.
You need to call the police or I will.
I won't let him hurt you.
If I succeed, I can't risk connecting here again.
If I don't, well. The dead don't do much talking.
You will be safe there and receive the treatment you need.
You came to me for help.
I think I got what I needed, actually.
All I've ever had is my brother and my books.
He and I are sick, aren't we?
You need to give me more time.
You know, I'm probably too far gone anyway.
I guess I knew it all along.
But I don't feel guilty anymore.
I need to protect you from my brother.
That could redeem me, couldn't it?
I think I heard his truck.
Give me liberty or give me death, right?
Not fiction, of course, but fitting to the task at hand.
You know, your husband did look a bit like me.
